<br>
&gt;&gt;&gt;The Sqaure helm I knew had to be a mistake. It is droped in SS, but...A lvl 47 mob drops it, if I remember right<br>
<br>
<br>
Huh?! Why shouldn't these items have these effects? Seriously will any group start wanting a caster instead of a melee even if we have every single one of the level 3 focus effects? Probably not. Wouldn't a level 1-44 char pretty much have access to every one of these effects at pretty cheap prices? Would caster heavy exp groups start performing better, or even on par with melee heavy ones? Nope. Why can melee's get better haste or better weps with a single group, but we need a raid?<br>
<br>
Like I said in another thread, pretty much any exp group that wants to max exp gain is looking at chanter, cleric, 4 duel-wield classes, maybe a shaman if teh chanter doesn't like to slow or backup heals might be needed. How are these effects inappropriate when they are far less than enough to bring us up to where we should be? People are just so used to casters sucking that any REAL step in the right direction is unthinkable. Rule of thumb, if you used the word 'Trivialize' to argue against a proposed idea to balance a caster class, you are probably a victim of the &quot;we deserve to suck&quot; mindset.<br>
<br>
If this is supposed to be a step towards caster balance then these effects need to drop off stuff we can actually kill and not just on raids where all the good stuff is gonna go to the clerics, chanters and shaman anyway, unless you're on dkp. <br>
<br>
They need to double the value of half the focus effects and REMOVE the level restrictions. Yep all three levels should work with all spells from 1 - 60, the level 1 items should have the current values, the level 2 items should have 50 % more and the level 3 should have double the current values. Then this would have been a real step towards balancing casters as compared to melee. <br>
<br>
<br>
I was 50 when Kunark came out, I've waited since that month for changes to come to bring casters back into line with melees. This patch could have been a real step in that direction but as it stands, with the good effects that work with level 45-60 spells being so few and hard to get again the uber get more uber, the twinked get more twinked and the non-essential casters watch all the best stuff go to the big 3 casters. People are gonna see &quot;healing bonus&quot; and boom Grats cleric, regardless of the fact that it's not gonna make any difference to any healer besides a druid.<br>
<br>
I just hope that they are merely taking it slow to be cautious and that we'll be seeing an upgrade to the power and availability of focus items very soon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utalyenatrueheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talyena Trueheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/02 9:17:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27534.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shadel Bandit Ring - Message I sent to Verant</span><hr size=1> &quot;I'm rather certain that the change they made to the Shadel Bandit Ring isn't a mistake. It's a relatively low level zone so the rewards shouldn't be for 60s.&quot;<br>
